# Implementation Plan - Publishing and Packaging ForecastAgent 1.0

This plan outlines the steps and code structure required to package **ForecastAgent 1.0** as a professional, redistributable Python package, document the Hugging Face model publishing workflow, and automate the creation of a GitHub repository under the user's account (`shinydatatech@gmail.com`).

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **GitHub Authentication & Credentials**: 
> Creating a repository on GitHub under `shinydatatech@gmail.com` requires a GitHub Personal Access Token (PAT) with `repo` scope. Since no local Git credentials or `gh` CLI credentials are currently configured on this system, we will create a helper script `scripts/create_github_repo.py` that prompts you for your PAT securely, uses it to create the remote repository, configures git locally, and pushes the code.

> [!NOTE]
> **Model Standalone Weights**:
> The package is designed to load model weights directly. In the publishing guide, we detail how to upload the standalone weights `model.ckpt` and config `model-config.yaml` to Hugging Face. The Python package will be configured to automatically download these weights from the Hugging Face Hub if they are not cached locally.

